4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING A COAL-FIRED GENERATING UNIT OPERATOR TO
5 PROVIDE PERPETUAL ACCESS TO WATER FOR AN ATTENDANT CITY OR TOWN; AND CLARIFYING
6 REQUIRING THE OPERATOR TO DEMONSTRATE THE FINANCIAL ASSURANCE NECESSARY TO
7 PROVIDE WATER TO AN ATTENDANT CITY OR TOWN; REVISING A DEFINITION; AND AMENDING
8 SECTIONS 75-8-103 AND 75-10-721, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 (Refer to Introduced Bill)
13 Strike everything after the enacting clause and insert:
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Water supply for city or town -- coal-fired generation -- perpetual
16 access. (1) Subject to the provisions of subsection (2), the operator of a coal-fired generating unit shall provide
17 the water supply for residential and commercial use of the city or town in which the coal-fired generating unit is
18 located to ensure an adequate water supply is available if a coal-fired generating unit closes or retires,
19 potentially jeopardizing access to a water supply.
20 (2) If the operator of a coal-fired generating unit owns, operates, or both owns and operates a
21 conveyance necessary to maintain a public water supply system as defined in 75-6-102, the operator shall
22 provide operation of the conveyance and access to the necessary water supply until contamination from the
23 coal-fired generating unit or its impoundments meets the department's cleanup criteria at the point of
24 compliance pursuant to Title 75, chapter 20.
25 (3) The operator of a coal-fired generating unit shall demonstrate to a local government attendant
26 to a coal-fired generating unit the financial assurance to provide the necessary water supply to the local
27 government 30 years after final remediation, including operating of, access to, and maintenance of the water
28 supply.
